translated: René Coty, born March 20, 1882 in Le Havre, and died November 22, 1962 in Le Havre, is a politician, who was from 1953 to 1959, the second and last president of the Fourth Republic.
original: René Coty, né le 20 mars 1882 au Havre, et mort le 22 novembre 1962 au Havre, est un homme politique, qui fut, de 1953 à 1959, le second et ultime président de la IVe République.
